    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-12T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-12T07:00:00-05:00" n="668"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94114 Mail/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-12T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 12, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1065. Department’s 617, July 28, 10 p.m. A note was sent to the Foreign Office on
                    July 29 requesting its urgent attention to the question of arranging for the
                    transmission of prisoners of war mail and the matter has subsequently twice been
                    discussed orally. On August 10 a Foreign Office official stated that this matter
                    should never have been arranged between the two Post Office departments and that
                    the Foreign Office was sending the Embassy a note to the effect that the Soviet
                    Government would be glad to arrange for the transmission of the mail in question
                    as soon as the United States and Japan reached an agreement on the subject. He
                    stated that Great Britain has such an agreement with Japan.</p>
                <p>The note to which he referred has not yet been received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
